<subSubSection id="C35B6530FF187AC9FF36FAB4FE8DF852" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFE36BBFF187AC9FF36FAB4FE3BF9BC" blockId="200.[189,1399,1339,1542]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FEC9FAB4FB98FAEF" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[322,451,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FEC9FAB4FB98FAEF" box="[322,451,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Modisimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is species rich in 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FD2BFAB4F8A6FAEF" box="[672,765,1339,1365]" name="Mexico" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Central America and the Antilles. Unpublished data suggest that the 79 extant species formally described from this region are just a small fraction of the actual diversity. For example, a recent collecting trip in 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FCDEFA0DF9F4FA26" box="[853,943,1410,1436]" name="Mexico" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<date id="FFFF107BFF187AC9FC34FA0DFE6CFA26" box="[959,1079,1410,1436]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" value="2019-10">Oct. 2019</date>
) resulted in ~33 species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FF36FA2AFB65FA05" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[189,318,1445,1471]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FF36FA2AFB65FA05" box="[189,318,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Modisimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which ~28 (i.e., 85%) are considered new (B.A. Huber, A. Valdez M., unpubl. data); extensive collections in the Caribbean (mostly 
<date id="FFFF107BFF187AC9FD62FA47F935FA58" box="[745,878,1480,1506]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" value="2011" valueMax="2014">2011–2014</date>
) resulted in ~98 species, of which ~72 (i.e., 73%) are considered new (B.A. Huber, I. Agnarsson, G. Binford, unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36BBFF187AC9FF36F9A2FEDFF8A1" blockId="200.[189,1399,1581,1819]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
By contrast, available data suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FD18F9A2F94FF9FD" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[659,788,1581,1607]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FD18F9A2F94FF9FD" box="[659,788,1581,1607]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Modisimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly represented in South America. Only three species have previously been reported from mainland South America: the pantropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FB6AF9DEFB34F937" authority="(Simon, 1893)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="culicinus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FB6AF9DEFF2CF9D0" box="[1249,1399,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">M. culicinus</emphasis>
(Simon, 1893)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FEF4F9FBF8C7F937" authority="Huber, 1997" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="1997" box="[383,668,1651,1677]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FEF4F9FBFBA2F937" box="[383,505,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">M. simoni</emphasis>
Huber, 1997
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FD67F9FCF93EF937" box="[748,869,1651,1677]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Venezuela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Venezuela</taxonomicName>
[including its junior synonym 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FB6CF9FBFBB6F90B" authority="(Gonzalez-Sponga, 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez-Sponga" baseAuthorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FB6CF9FBFF2DF937" box="[1255,1398,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">M. minimus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B4AFF187AC9FF4EF919FBBEF90B" author="Gonzalez-Sponga M. A." box="[197,485,1686,1713]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref127402" refString="Gonzalez-Sponga M. A. 2009. Aracnidos de Venezuela. Cuatro nuevos generos y cinco especies nuevas de la familia Pholcidae (Araneae). Anartia 21: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2009">González-Sponga, 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; see below]; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FD3EF918F9AFF90B" authority="Schmidt, 1956" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1956" box="[693,1012,1686,1713]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Physocyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FD3EF918F918F90A" box="[693,835,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">M. globosus</emphasis>
Schmidt, 1956
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FBB1F919FEE9F90A" box="[1082,1202,1686,1712]" name="Colombia" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. A fourth species is newly described below. The faunal turnovers seem to lie somewhere in the 
<collectingRegion id="4985F859FF187AC9FBBEF935FEDEF96E" box="[1077,1157,1722,1748]" country="Panama" name="Darien" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Darien</collectingRegion>
Gap linking 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FA91F935FF2CF96E" box="[1306,1399,1722,1748]" name="Panama" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FF66F952FB3AF94D" box="[237,353,1757,1783]" name="Colombia" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and between the Lesser Antilles (which have a rich unpublished fauna) and 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FB44F952FF68F94D" box="[1231,1331,1757,1783]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
(with no representative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FE26F88FF875F8A0" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[429,558,1792,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FE26F88FF875F8A0" box="[429,558,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Modisimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FD02F88EF941F8A0" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[649,794,1792,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="culicinus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FD02F88EF941F8A0" box="[649,794,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">M. culicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known to exist in collections).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36BBFF187AC9FF36F8CDFE8DF852" blockId="200.[189,1399,1857,2025]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
To some degree, this marked turnover is probably artificial. The pholcid fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FB2EF8CEFF42F8E1" box="[1189,1305,1857,1883]" name="Colombia" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Colombia</collectingCountry>
is very poorly known, and the near-coastal regions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FD7DF8EAF934F8C5" box="[758,879,1893,1919]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Venezuela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Venezuela</taxonomicName>
may also be home to further species. It is unknown whether 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FF187AC9FE10F807F847F818" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[411,540,1928,1954]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FF187AC9FE10F807F847F818" box="[411,540,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Modisimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been largely replaced by other taxa in South America or whether it has colonized South America via 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FDC8F823F8FBF87C" box="[579,672,1964,1990]" name="Panama" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Panama</collectingCountry>
and the Lesser Antilles. The apparent absence of relict species (e.g., in caves and arid regions of 
<collectingCountry id="F356762BFF187AC9FDC0F841F8CFF853" box="[587,660,1998,2025]" name="Brazil" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) suggests that the second scenario is more likely.
</paragraph>
